{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012ow9E5Rj8gSZFWCzcLedYU","type":"tool_result","content":"   900→| 13 | 3 | 0 | 3 (Docker) |\n   901→| 14 | 1 | 1 | 0 (3 skipped) |\n   902→\n   903→Sessions 11-14 show a clear pattern: infrastructure failures (Docker, disk space) throttle verification throughput. Dev and code-review velocity remain high, but the \"done\" gate is bottlenecked. Session 14's approach of skipping blocked stories and completing what's possible is the healthiest response, but the 3 stuck stories need a resolution policy.\n   904→\n   905→---\n   906→\n   907→# Session Retrospective — 2026-03-25 (Session 15)\n   908→\n   909→**Appended:** 2026-03-25T09:48Z\n   910→**Sprint:** Operational Excellence (Epic 14-15 — Tech Debt Pipeline + Code Quality)\n   911→**Session:** 15\n   912→**Session window:** ~2026-03-25 02:05 UTC to ~2026-03-25 05:48 UTC (~4 hours)\n   913→**Ralph runs:** 2 (first run: iterations 1-13, ~4h40m; second run: iteration 1+, ~15m before this retro)\n   914→\n   915→---\n   916→\n   917→## 1. Session Summary\n   918→\n   919→| Story | Epic | Outcome | Commit Time (UTC+4) | Notes |\n   920→|-------|------|---------|---------------------|-------|\n   921→| 14-2-tech-debt-gate-story-selection | Epic 14 | done | 02:40 | Clean pass |\n   922→| 14-3-docker-precheck-orphan-cleanup | Epic 14 | done | 02:58 | 1 retry |\n   923→| 14-7-fix-beads-flags-ralph-tracking-proof-docs | Epic 14 | done | 04:44 | Clean pass |\n   924→| 15-1-ci-file-size-gate | Epic 15 | done | 04:58 | Clean pass |\n   925→| 15-2-eslint-no-empty-catch-boundary-tests | Epic 15 | done | 05:41 | Clean pass |\n   926→| 15-3-template-migration-static-files | Epic 15 | done | 09:45 | 1 retry, completed in 2nd ralph run |\n   927→| 15-4-fix-ts-compilation-errors | Epic 15 | review | — | Story created + dev done, not yet committed |\n   928→| 14-4-observability-backend-choice | Epic 14 | stuck | — | Exceeded retry limit (10+), flagged |\n   929→| 14-5-stack-aware-verify-dockerfile | Epic 14 | stuck | — | 8+ retries across session, never completed |\n   930→| 14-6-subagent-status-ownership-time-budget | Epic 14 | stuck | — | Still in verifying, no progress |\n   931→\n   932→**Net progress:** 6 stories completed (done). 1 in review. 3 stuck in verifying. Overall sprint: 61 of 66 stories done (92%). 5 remaining.\n   933→\n   934→---\n   935→\n   936→## 2. Issues Analysis\n   937→\n   938→### Bugs Discovered During Implementation\n   939→\n   940→| Severity | Story | Issue | Fixed? |\n   941→|----------|-------|-------|--------|\n   942→| MEDIUM | 15-4 | `dimensions.ts` used `g.message` and `g.fix` — nonexistent properties on the actual object. Runtime bug (undefined values). Changed to `g.description`, removed `g.fix`. | Yes |\n   943→| MEDIUM | 15-4 | `run.ts` used `'in-review'` string literal but `StoryStatus` type only has `'review'`. Other system parts (bash/yaml) may still use `'in-review'` — cross-system inconsistency. | Partially — TS fixed, bash/yaml not audited |\n   944→| LOW | 15-4 | `docker-setup.ts` writes `opensearch` property not in `HarnessState` interface. Used `as HarnessState` cast to suppress. | Workaround only |\n   945→\n   946→### Workarounds Applied (Tech Debt Introduced)\n   947→\n   948→| Story | Workaround | Debt Level |\n   949→|-------|-----------|------------|"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01S47kpRLEHAaTk7ghFbnaxm","session_id":"ac7c4ad3-ab82-45bf-800b-229e9ebcd932","uuid":"af651555-6ee2-4ffa-b59a-ae5f53d6926f","timestamp":"2026-03-25T07:57:09.264Z"}
